Step 1. Calculate the Gross Profit Margin using the income statement.  
• Gross Profit = 194172.30  
• Total Revenue = 547392.30  
Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 = (194172.30 / 547392.30) × 100 ≈ 35.49%

Step 2. Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio using the cash flow statement and balance sheet.  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -2868695.86  
• Total Current Liabilities (from balance sheet) = 5042389.63  
Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities = -2868695.86 / 5042389.63 ≈ -0.57

Thus, the solution is:
{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "35.49%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-0.57"
  }
